two been gone a while?

577
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:19,760
This has been real
and fun, but I got to go.

578
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,360
Oh, my God.

579
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,120
This isn't what it looks like.

580
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,720
Other members say our abductor's
been coming the last month.

581
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:08,000
Said his name was Tod,
but group protocol

582
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:09,920
requires they remain anonymous.

583
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,320
So no real ID.

584
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:12,760
And the guy you shot,
the one with the pigs?

585
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:14,200
Prints came back career criminal.

586
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,480
Probably just the muscle.
The other guy was in charge.

587
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,000
He knew there was a cop
there at the meeting.

588
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,440
He still took her.

589
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:22,160
That's cold or crazy.

590
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:24,720
Either way, he's almost
sure to follow the same M.O.

591
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:26,960
He'll confront Miss Mullens
with her greatest fear.

592
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:29,320
- Which is drowning.
- Specifically in a pool.

593
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,960
There's hundreds of pools in Gotham.

594
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:33,320
- We can't possibly get to every...
- That was her mother.

595
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,000
When she was seven,
Scottie almost drowned

596
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,800
in Lemmars Park pool uptown.

597
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,040
It's a start, I guess.

598
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:39,360
That's where he took her,
I can feel it.

599
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:45,760
- Boss?
- Oh, not now, Joe. Wait.

600
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:49,640
Tell me that's not
what it looks like.

601
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:55,040
You're brave.

602
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:57,720
I'd say you're an eight
on the Crane Scale.

603
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,720
Profound fear.

604
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:06,160
Twelve is top.
Abject heart-stopping terror.

605
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:08,840
I'm surprised you're only an eight.

606
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:11,760
You do understand
that this is really happening?

607
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,360
I'm going to drown you.

608
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,400
Right now.

609
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:22,120
There! That's a ten.

610
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:24,840
Dad.

611
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:29,000
Jonathan, I said to wait in the van.

612
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,280
The parking meter ran out.

613
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:39,280
Look, son, I know this hard,
but we talked about it.

614
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:41,960
It's for the common good,
for humanity.

615
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:46,000
I know. I just... I think...

616
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:49,000
This will be over soon. Here.

617
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:50,520
Go and feed the meter.

618
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,360
Go on, go.

619
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:05,360
Now, my dear,
don't think badly of me.

620
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,440
GCPD!

621
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:34,240
Don't move!

622
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,520
I'm on him! You get her!

623
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,640
He's alive. I told you he was alive.

624
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:12,200
Praise the Lord.

625
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,800
Glory be.

626
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:17,640
What happened to you, boy?

627
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:22,240
Like the prodigal son, ma'am,
I have fallen.

628
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:24,760
Like Job,
I've been tested in the deepest pits

629
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:27,560
of the devil's perfidy and survived.

630
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,840
Lord have mercy.

631
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:37,440
Are you headed to Gotham City,
by any chance?

632
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:38,720
Sure.

633
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,200
Come on.

634
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:43,560
<i>- Trouble in my way
- Trouble in my way</i>

635
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:47,400
<i>- I got to cry sometimes
- I got to cry sometimes</i>

636
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:51,720
<i>- I lay awake at night
- I lay awake at night</i>

637
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:53,680
<i>But that's all right, it's all right</i>

638
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:55,560
<i>That's all right</i>

639
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:57,240
<i>'Cause Jesus will fix it</i>

640
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:59,400
<i>Jesus will fix it</i>

641
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:02,280
<i>- After a while
- After</i>

642
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:16,800
Case files you gave me about that man
who was thrown from the roof.

643
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,320
Did you catch his killer yet?

644
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:19,960
Oh, no. He's still out there.

645
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:21,400
- Hi.
- I followed up,

646
00:39:21,480 --> 00:39:23,000
and I had a quick look at his corpse.

647
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:24,240
A quick look at his corpse?

648
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,360
Yeah, its' just downstairs
at the morgue. No trouble.

649
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,160
So the killer removed
his adrenal glands.

650
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:29,720
Adrenal glands? That's strange.

651
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,240
They have no value on
the black market, do they?

652
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:34,600
No. Kidneys and livers, yes.
Adrenal glands, no.

653
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,440
It produces cortisol,
the hormone that gives us

654
00:39:37,520 --> 00:39:40,520
that adrenalized
fight-or-flight reaction.

655
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,600
Essentially, it's the fear gland.

656
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:44,680
And our man
wants to take it from the victim

657
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:46,800
when he's most fearful. Why do that?

658
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:49,360
All I can think
of is that at the moment of death,

659
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:51,880
the victim's adrenals
would produce a massive,

660
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:53,600
highly-elevated form of cortisol.

661
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,280
Fascinating, huh?

662
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:57,040
This is one weird dude.

663
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:59,720
A doctor or a nurse, most likely.

664
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:02,560
